<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="405" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1653]" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1483,1509]" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Ariyama &amp; Kohtsuka, 2022" authorityName="Ariyama &amp; Kohtsuka" authorityYear="2022" box="[321,564,1483,1509]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Aoroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sagamiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[321,564,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Aoroides sagamiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[571,659,1483,1509]" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[571,659,1483,1509]" pageId="12" pageNumber="405" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a distinctive male gnathopod 1 with poorly setose basis and heavily setose merus. Only 
<taxonomicName authority="Ariyama, 2004" authorityName="Ariyama" authorityYear="2004" box="[409,782,1519,1545]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Aoroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubellus">
<emphasis box="[409,608,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Aoroides rubellus</emphasis>
Ariyama, 2004
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[850,914,1519,1545]" name="Japan" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Japan</collectingCountry>
shares such a gnathopod 
<quantity box="[1202,1245,1519,1545]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="12" pageNumber="405" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
the genus. However, this new species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ariyama" authorityYear="2004" box="[698,821,1555,1581]" class="Malacostraca" family="Aoridae" genus="Aoroides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="12" pageNumber="405" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubellus">
<emphasis box="[698,821,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">A. rubellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the fewer robust setae on the uropods 1–3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,1653]" box="[199,777,1590,1617]" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1590,1616]" pageId="12" pageNumber="405">Habitat.</emphasis>
Gravel and sand bottom, 
<quantity box="[587,700,1591,1617]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="10.3" metricValueMin="8.7" pageId="12" pageNumber="405" unit="m" value="95.0" valueMax="103.0" valueMin="87.0">87–103 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
